des:
The Galaxy Lamps App lets you control your Galaxy Lamps devices. You can simply ask Alexa to turn on or turn off your Galaxy Projector.
Use voice to control your Galaxy Lamps devices - just talk to Alexa on your Amazon Echo.
After connecting Alexa to your Galaxy Lamps devices in a few simple steps:
(1). Download our Galaxy Lamps App in the Android or IOS App store;
(2). Sign up for an account in our Galaxy Lamps App;
(3). You need to have a Galaxy Lamps device in hand;
(4). Configure these devices in our Galaxy Lamps App and change appropriate name for your devices which will be used in Galaxy Lamps skills;
(5). Download the Amazon Alexa App from Android, IOS or Amazon App store;
(6). Configure Echo with Alexa App;
(7). Search Galaxy Lamps skill from the Alexa app skills category;
(8). Click Enable skill of Galaxy Lamps, and you'll be navigated to App name login page;
(9). Input your Galaxy Lamps App account username and password;
(10). Setup is now complete.

You can enjoy the voice control on your home devices like these:
“Alexa, turn on the Galaxy Lamp.”
“Alexa, turn off the Galaxy Lamp.”
“Alexa, set the Galaxy Lamp to 50%.”
“Alexa, brighten the Galaxy Lamp to 50%.”
“Alexa, dim the Galaxy Lamp to 50%.”
"Alexa, Galaxy Lamp to green."
"Alexa, set Galaxy Lamp to cool white."
